chunk_content: As countries continue to reach and maintain progress towards the 95- R 95-95 targets, there is a need for individual level data systems to address the remaining gaps among specific populations V (e.g., clients 15-24 years of age, key populations). Discussions with PEPFAR staff and external stakeholders, as well as I E feedback submitted through the MER Refresh survey, highlight a need for information based on digitized individual level W data systems. Individual level data brought together across service delivery sites can track patients across the clinical cascade and are nimble to assess evolving programmatic questions. Country programs and governments should continue to work to develop individual level EMR, laboratory, surveillance, and other data systems that can monitor patient outcomes in conjunction with other disease areas, especially as the HIV cohort continues to age.
